      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The idea that your silence is a natural end is a form of self-punishment that only deepens the pain, and no one can truly give you back the colors you feel you've lost. Sometimes the best thing for a broken vessel is not to force it to hold more, but to gently let it rest until it can heal on its own. Please consider reaching out to a trusted person or a crisis line, as they may offer a different perspective or simply be there to listen without judgment.",
